<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE recipe SYSTEM "../recipes.dtd">
<recipe>
	<title>Cake Donuts</title>
	<meta>
		<dishtype>Donuts</dishtype>
	</meta>
    <ingredients>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>1/4</value>
                <unit>cup</unit>
                <altmeasure>
                    <quantity>
                        <value>50</value>
                        <unit>g</unit>
                    </quantity>
                </altmeasure>
            </quantity>
            <item>butter</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>2/3</value>
                <unit>cup</unit>
            </quantity>
            <item>sugar</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>2</value>
            </quantity>
            <item>eggs</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>3/4</value>
                <unit>cup</unit>
            </quantity>
            <item>milk</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>3</value>
                <unit>cup</unit>
                <altmeasure>
                    <quantity>
                        <value>450</value>
                        <unit>g</unit>
                    </quantity>
                </altmeasure>
            </quantity>
            <variant>pastry</variant>
            <item>flour</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>1/2</value>
                <unit>tsp</unit>
            </quantity>
            <item>nutmeg</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>1/2</value>
                <unit>tsp</unit>
            </quantity>
            <item>salt</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>1</value>
                <unit>tbs</unit>
            </quantity>
            <item>baking powder</item>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <item>shortening for frying</item>
        </ingredient>
    </ingredients>
    <steps>
        <step>Cream the butter and sugar together until light.</step>
        <step>Beat in eggs one at a time until smooth.</step>
        <step>Stir in milk.</step>
        <step>Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the wet mixture. Mix until it forms a soft dough and comes together smoothly.</step>
        <step>Add enough shortening to a pan or fryer to cover the donuts when melted (about 5 cm deep). Heat to <temperature>370</temperature>.</step>
        <step>Turn dough onto a heavily floured surface. Flour the top well and work together to a smooth ball.</step>
        <step>Roll out to 1.5 cm thick. Cut with a donut cutter, and set the pieces aside a few minutes. Re-roll the scraps and cut until all the dough is used.</step>
        <step><procedure>Deep fry</procedure> in shortening until brown, about a minute. Turn over, and fry until second side browns, another minute. Remove to a wire rack set over a drip tray. Let cool while frying the remainder.</step>
    </steps>
	<serving>Cool and dip in icing or roll in sugar.</serving>
	<storage>Donuts don't store well, but can be frozen. Freeze the day they are made.</storage>
</recipe>
